posts.title: Still haven’t accepted it. Glad to have been here all these years with you frens.
posts.content:
So many mixed feelings over the last many years. Especially the last few months. I couldn’t consider the possibility of beating the rig after the 2020 debacle, though I desperately wanted it to happen. Likewise I thought for sure the summer of love 2.0 would immediately begin after Trump won again. And surely right after that, Biden would get us into another world war before he could even take office. Or they’d try to take him out again before inauguration. No way would they EVER allow him in the Oval Office again. Yet here he is…back up in their ass with the resurrection.

I still haven’t accepted it. I’m still pondering what the next psyop shit show false flag hoax is that they are going to pull out. It’s like PTSD after years of abuse. It will take a long time, if ever, to untrain this conditioning - a problem I am grateful to need to work on!

It has been terrific to have this community. It might be the only thing that saved me from the nut house. Many of us have nothing in common - except a belief that DJT can save our republic from the rotting and decaying mess it has become. Just knowing that there are huge numbers of us and that we are not alone carried me and my family through so many dark nights. I am thankful for all of you…even the faggots and handshakes that try to shill here. It has kept me sane.

As awful as times were for years, I can see a lot of really good things that happened along the way. For one, this bullshit caused me to seek a new career that allows me to do something about it. And the shitty economic circumstances over those years freed up my time enough to where I could actually embark on that journey. My family and I are not the same people we were 5 years ago…and through it all we are somehow in a better place than before it started. It couldn’t have worked out like this without you all and PDW. My sincerest gratitude goes out to all of you frens.
